					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-macleod" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1922529); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1922529&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164737" alt="Agent MacLeod" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1922529)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-macleod" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1922529); return false;" >Agent MacLeod</a></span> <span class="odate time_1444719009 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Oct 2015 06:50</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2390695">
									

<p>Can I add the Are We Cool Yet? tag? I'm assuming the loathed logo mentioned in the story is &quot;Are We Cool Yet?&quot;</p>
<p>This is much more refined than the draft I read (and didn't critique). It leaves a lot of questions, but it also tells us exactly what we need to know. It doesn't tell us what emotion to feel, but it does make the reader feel emotion. It does still have some aspect of its weird &quot;this came in a dream&quot; quality to it, which serves it well enough.</p>
<p>Overall, good job, sirpudding. If this is your first tale, it's definitely a good way to get started; it also feels like a meta story critiquing AWCY? as a GOI/in-universe movement, which seems to be in-vogue now, but this takes advantage of it without feeling like the whole point is &quot;I made fun of AWCY?. Am I cool yet?&quot; I feel like <em>that</em> is gonna become a trend pretty soon, but this is ahead of that curve and therefore doesn't feel, well, like it's trying to be cool. Because it isn't trying, it simply is. Eugh, I'm digressing. Here, this is an appropriately disturbing story, you've earned your upvote.</p>

							</div>

								
					
