															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1324229"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1444745234 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Oct 2015 14:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2390837">
									

<p>This is <em>alright</em>. The stuff with Petra was kind of interesting, and I would be interested to see if you go anywhere with it.</p>
<p>Overall, though, it's more of the same &quot;elder critic scolds the younguns for being so foolish and nihilistic and generally awful hipsters&quot; narrative that has become the default for anything relating to Are We Cool Yet?, as well as pretty much anything relating to art more generally (see also: <a href="/critiquing-a-cardboard-box">Critiquing a Cardboard Box</a> for the most recent example). It's a theme that has come up time and time again, and by this point is more than a little tiresome.</p>
<p>Honestly, if we're going to keep with this trend of AWCY-as-meta-commentary, I prefer that it go in a direction other than &quot;newbies amirite?&quot;</p>
<p>Despite some interesting touches and some good imagery, it's just too samey for my tastes. -1</p>

							</div>

								
