			<div class="content" id="post-content-2404675">
									

<p>I like this. I really do.</p>
<p>I've seen and helped clean up countless cock-ups, mystical and mundane, and strikes a serious chord with me. From the context, I assume Petra is a sort of &quot;embodiment of the Inner City&quot;? An egregoric manifestation? (I know you described her as a Tulpa.)</p>
<p>One tiny nitpick/typo spot: &quot;Jack Parson's Babylon&quot;, towards the end. That really should be Babalon.</p>
<p>Upvoted for really keeping my attention!</p>

